    "Secondary features.",
    "Secondary features are defined as those features that can provide an added advantage but are not critical in the context of SMEs.",
    "For example, the built-in data sources provided by the SIEM solution may be enough for an SME.",
    "As the size of these organizations is not very large, a highly scalable solution is usually not a primary requirement.",
    "Vulnerability scanners are commonly available as standalone products and are already used by most SMEs, therefore the availability of vulnerability scanning capability as part of SIEM is not of primary importance."
